article.headline: Portland St. 92, Cal Poly-SLO 83
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Dominic Waters scored 32 points to lead Portland State to a 92-83 win over Cal Poly on Saturday night. Melvin Jones added 16 points for the Vikings (1-3), who gave coach Tyler Geving his first career victory. Jamie Jones scored 13 points and Phil Nelson had 11. Lorenzo Keeler led Cal Poly (0-3) with 20 points. Will Donahue added 14 points and Charles Anderson had 13 off the bench. PSU led by as many as 13 points in the first half before Cal Poly rallied in the second half to take a 71-70 lead with 7:01 left to play. The Vikings regained the lead on a Waters jumper with 6:28 remaining and held off the Mustangs down the stretch. Portland State shot 67 percent from the field and held Cal Poly to 40-percent shooting. The Mustangs outrebounded PSU 31-20.
